@@TJvWizardFrameStyle
<TITLE TJvWizardFrameStyle type>
Summary
  Defines available wizard frame styles.
Description
  TJvWizardFrameStyle is used to define the styles that JvWizardDrawBorderEdges can draw in.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardFrameStyle.fsWindows
  Draw frames using default Windows style.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardFrameStyle.fsNone
  Don't draw any frame.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardFrameStyle.fsFlat
  Draw frames using a single gray line.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardFrameStyle.fsGroove
  Draw frames with a double lowered edge.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardFrameStyle.fsBump
  Draw frames with a double raised edge.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardFrameStyle.fsLowered
  Draw frames with a lowered edge.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvWizardFrameStyle.fsRaised
  Draw frames with a raised edge.

